.TH "devm_phy_package_join" 9 "devm_phy_package_join" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
devm_phy_package_join \- resource managed phy_package_join()
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" devm_phy_package_join
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct phy_device *phydev "  ","
.BI "int addr "  ","
.BI "size_t priv_size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
device that is registering this PHY package
.IP "phydev" 12
target phy_device struct
.IP "addr" 12
cookie and PHY address for global register access
.IP "priv_size" 12
if non-zero allocate this amount of bytes for private data
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Managed \fBphy_package_join\fP. Shared storage fetched by this function,
\fBphy_package_leave\fP is automatically called on driver detach. See
\fBphy_package_join\fP for more information.
